cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.MM 

The paper deals with image classification using Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) and proposes a new dataset for weather classification. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of data augmentation techniques and the evaluation of different CNN architectures, which are common topics in the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions the use of super pixel delimiting masks, which is a technique used in image segmentation, making cs.IR (Information Retrieval) another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with image datasets, which is a topic in cs.MM (Multimedia).
